Rev, and Sirenia - WOW so many ideas to digest!  Excellent work in such a short period of time.<br>
<br>
OK from the top, GL's - I agree on having 3 GL's for all the same reasons, no power mongering , having one on line, voting, etc.  I really agree with Sirenia on the &quot;one main&quot; GL for direction and vision and the other two GL's for checks and balance.<br>
<br>
I also agree with Sirenia on the 2/3 voting majority.  Leadership is a great responsibility and needs the attention and respect it deserves.  As Sirenia said, &quot;... the election of any GL is a powerful undertaking and should be treated as such.&quot;  Voting for GL office positions at different times is a wise move for just the reasons Sirenia said.<br>
<br>
Quick question Sirenia - do you hold public office or are you going to in the near future? LOL <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   You sound like a someone who has held public office.<br>
<br>
I like the rank structure with the following idea changes:<br>
<br>
9) Trial members - Guild chat access only ( must prove themselves)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Full members - Guild chat, Emblem, voting, guild donations (or taxes) (must maintain good standing as                              outlined in guild charter)<br>
<br>
6) Class Elders - Guild chat, Emblem, voting, guild donations (or taxes) (must maintain good standing as                                 outlined in guild charter) Provides advice and answers questions within their class.<br>
<br>
4) Officers - (or replace with other titles i.e. Captains) Guild chat, Officer chat Emblem, voting, guild                     donation (or taxes),  raid leaders for PvE, (must maintain good standing as outlined in guild                     charter) Carries out duties defined by GL or Counsel of Founders.  Provides direct                     leadership in resolving disputes.<br>
<br>
Notice I didn't say Officers should be able to disburse funds.  I think to many people able to extract funds, even with &quot;stringent requirements&quot;, is inherently dangerous.<br>
<br>
3) Treasurers, Ambassadors, Tax Collectors, Sheriff, RvR raid leaders (?), Guild Scribe, Counselor, Jester,                      etc - Guild chat, Emblem, Officer chat, Voting, Guild donation (or Taxes) and dispersal                      (Treasurers and Tax collectors) Alliance chat ( Ambassadors), Invite/Remove (Sheriff),                      Counsel voting rights, Promote/demote (Sergeant at Arms ?)<br>
<br>
1) Founders - Guild chat, Officer chat, Emblem, guild donation ( or Taxes), disperse guild funds (within                                               guidelines), alliance chat, invite/remove, promote/demote, general voting, counsel voting.                        (Must maintain good standing as outlined in guild charter) Must carry out the duties of                        office ensuring the strategic vision of the guild is followed. Assist all other members in                        disputes, answering questions, and offering advice. Assist GL (GL's) as required.<br>
<br>
0) GL's - Well heck, they get to do everything! <br>
<br>
Alternate naming conventions ( to keep in line with game)<br>
<br>
9) Privates<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Corporals<br>
6) Sergeants<br>
4) Captains<br>
3) Various Titles (see above)<br>
1) Founders (Sir - Lady ?)<br>
0) GL ( Lord - Lady?)<br>
<br>
Sorry I'm not very imaginative in naming conventions.  Hmmm, not very imaginative in a lot of things. Oh well, that is a different story.  I'd go for court jester but I think Dallin has me beat.<br>
<br>
Hope this will help and that I was not to long winded.  I'm sure there will be more good ideas from others as well.<br>
